  "prompt": "How much did it cost Samsung to make the Galaxy S5 waterproof?",
  "response": "The precise cost incurred by Samsung to make the Galaxy S5 waterproof isn't publicly detailed in financial or manufacturing breakdowns. However, integrating waterproof technology generally involves additional expenses for research and development, specialized materials, design adjustments, and rigorous testing to meet waterproof standards.\n\nThe Galaxy S5, released in 2014, was rated IP67, indicating it was dust-tight and could withstand immersion in water up to 1 meter for 30 minutes. This required specific manufacturing techniques and components like gaskets and seals.\n\nFor exact figures, one would need internal cost analysis from Samsung, which is typically not disclosed publicly. However, it's widely understood that the waterproofing added to the overall production cost, which would have been factored into the retail price.",
